                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4480: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-14T00:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1931—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received July 15—5:16
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Reference is made to my telegram No. 82, July 14, 6 p.m. The Belgian
                    Government is now working out a formula for notification to the B. I. S. of
                    provisional postponement of German payments tomorrow.</p>
                <pb facs="0300" n="186" xml:id="pg_186"/>
                <p>The Belgian Government has formally accepted the British invitation to the London
                    Conference and is sending a delegation tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
